4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING FINES FOR ILLEGALLY TRANSPORTING AQUATIC
5 INVASIVE SPECIES; AND AMENDING SECTION 80-7-1014, MCA.”
6
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
8
9 Section 1. Section 80-7-1014, MCA, is amended to read:
10 "80-7-1014. Penalty. (1) Except as provided in subsection (2), the following penalties apply:
11 (a) The offense of negligently violating the provisions of 80-7-1010 through 80-7-1012 and 80-7-
12 1015 or rules adopted under 80-7-1010 through 80-7-1012 and 80-7-1015 pertaining to an invasive species
13 management area or the statewide invasive species management area is a misdemeanor punishable by a fine
14 not to exceed $500 $1,000 for the first offense and $750 $1,500 for subsequent offenses.
15 (b) The offense of purposely or knowingly violating the provisions of 80-7-1010 through 80-7-1012
16 and 80-7-1015 or rules adopted under 80-7-1010 through 80-7-1012 and 80-7-1015 pertaining to an invasive
17 species management area or the statewide invasive species management area is a misdemeanor punishable
18 by a fine not to exceed $975 $1,950. In addition, the person shall forfeit the following as issued by this state:
19 (i) any current fishing license and the privilege to fish in this state for a period of time set by the
20 court; and
21 (ii) any current sticker or decal required under this part to operate a vessel on the waters of this
22 state.
23 (c) Purposely or knowingly attempting to introduce an invasive species in Montana is a felony. Any
24 person found guilty under this subsection (1)(c) is subject to a criminal penalty of up to 2 years in prison, a fine
25 not to exceed $10,000, or both. A person convicted of violating this subsection (1)(c) may also be required to
26 surrender an involved vessel and pay restitution for any cost incurred to mitigate the effect of the violation.
27 (d) A civil penalty not to exceed $2,500 may be imposed on any person who violates any other
28 provision of 80-7-1010 through 80-7-1012 and 80-7-1015 or rules adopted under 80-7-1010 through 80-7-1012
